I actually own one of the same model.  Sure some of the the newer polymer .380 pistols are not that much bigger, and are lighter, but there is something to be said for the nice feeling in the hand of an all metal super simple designed pistol.   Designed in Italy, where most of the parts were made.  Due to the Gun Control Act of 1968, assembly was moved to Miami, where the imported parts were installed on a U.S. made frame.   Ultra small, but fun to shoot.   Includes one 7 rd. magazine. title: For Sale:  Very good condition Smith & Wesson 6904 9mm service quality all metal conceal carry pistol
postcontent: I have several of these (6906 stainless steel and 6904 blued version) fine generation three service quality conceal carry 9mm pistols, and can likely get a bunch more in the same good+ condition.  They are in very good shape, including the bores.   Might have been owned by Broward County Sheriff's Department, since they obviously weren't shot much.  All metal firearm. Totally reliable pistol. If you could figure out how to load their mags with beer cans, I bet  they would feed them with no problems  Super smooth and light trigger.   Very managable recoil. Traditional double and single action locked breech semi automatic pistol. Construction is steel barrel, slide assembly, internal parts, sights, trigger, hammer, levers, magazine body and innards, all built into a lightweight alloy frame. Only the grips, Mag safety plunger bushing, and magazine floorplate and follower are polymer. Barrel is 3 1/2 inch Devel type with ball joint muzzle collar that ensures accuracy and facilitates disassembly. Rifling is five groove right hand 1:18.75. Slide is serrated rear, .925 wide at the port; with ambidextrous safety levers that also decock the pistol. Slide also houses the firing pin and magazine safeties: the 6906 will not fire without magazine. Sights are matte blue steel dovetailed front and rear; dot front  These came from the factory with 12 round magazines.  My supplier didn't supply any magazines for them, but each will come with either one brand new flush fitting (with finger extension) 10 round magazine, or a nice used 12 round flush(with finger extension) fitting mag. 15 round mags are available for only $20, which seat well and are for the same 59 S&W series, but extend somewhat past the body of the pistol. I suggest getting it with the one flush fitting  mag, and getting the 15 round mag for $20 more. Its nice to have a 15 rounder for range time anyway.  I will not sell magazines separately without pistol purchase.
